A 20-year-old motorcyclist, Saminu Saidu, appeared before a Grade I Area Court, Lugbe in FCT on Friday for allegedly stealing a motorcycle belonging to one Murtar Garba. The Police charged Saidu of Tundu-Wada village, Lugbe, with a two-count charge of criminal joint act and theft. The Prosecution Counsel, Jibrin Seidu, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on July 31 and was reported on the same date by Garba. He alleged that the nominal complainant’s brother, Usman Garba, parked his red boxed Bajaj motorcycle with Engine number DU WKE 74942 and chassis number XMD 2A18AYIKWE97089 at the tipper garage in Lugbe. ALSO READ: Man remanded for alleged culpable homicide He said that he parked the motorcycle near the defendant’s own, to visit the brother – Garba and that when he returned his motorcycle had been stolen. He further said that the defendant said he saw another person with a yellow shirt taking the motorcycle away. The defendant, who does not understand English, pleaded not guilty in Hausa. The Presiding Judge, Abubakar Sadiq, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N200,000 with one surety in like sum. Sadiq ordered that the surety must be residing within the FCT and adjourned the case until Sept. 4 for hearing. (NAN)  YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE FG Spends N1.57trn On Debt Servicing, N1.61trn On Personnel, Pension THE Federal Government on Thursday disclosed that it had expended N1.57 trillion on debt servicing and N1.61 trillion on personnel and pensions in the current year.  The Minister of Finance, Budget and National Planning, Mrs Zainab Ahmed, made the statement on debt servicing and others expenses during the presentation of the  2021-2023 Medium-term Expenditure Framework (MTEF) and Fiscal  Strategy Paper… WhatsApp Business: An App Grossly Underused WhatsApp Business is an app designed for small businesses to easily stay in touch with their customers and reach out to potential customers. It provides vi